from dan a rose arise subject re national repentance mcovingt michael covington write i hear on the radio today about a christian student conference where christian be call to repent of america national sin such a sexual promiscuity to which i reply whoa there how can i repent of someone sin i ca and when i claim to repent of someone else sin be i not in fact judge him jesu equip u to judge activity but warn u not to judge person judge not that ye be not judge c s lewi make the same point in an essay after world war ius when some christian leader in britain be urge national repentance for the horror sin of world war ius i see ymy point but i can not more strongly disagree to repent mean to turn around we a a nation have behave incredibly arrogantly toward god condone encourage and even force folk to participate in activity directly oppose to the write word of god we have arrogantly set my nation far above the god who create it and allow u the luxury of live in thi land we have set a bad example for other nation we slaughter unborn child by the million we have stricken the name of god from the classroom we cheat god out of the honor due him at every turn and we owe god an apology every bite a public a my sin have be when jesu say judge not that ye be not judge he wa not address those like john the baptist who have repent and be call other to repent he wa address those who remain in sin while heap down condemnation on other for their sin hi message to u all wa to remove the log from my own eye before remove the speck from my brother but he also say to rebuke and to reprove do forget that thi be a command too my problem today be that we tend to judge and condemn a though we be rebuke and we tend to neglect bring folk back to the lord with the excuse that we do want to judge anyone in truth what we need to do be to judge le and call other to repent more and to be able to distinguish between the two in my own motive call sin what it be and do so openly let it charge fall correctly where it should but instead of run someone into hell over it pull them out of their hellward path and onto the heavenward path i deplore the horrible crime of child murder we want prevention not merely punishment we must reach the root of the evil it be practice by those whose inmost soul revolt from the dreadful deed no mater what the motive love of ease or a desire to save from suffer the unborn innocent the woman be awfully guilty who commit the deed but oh thrice guilty be he who drive her to the desperation which impel her to the crime susan b anthony the revolution july 